label.value: establishment of sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: The process in which the sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome become associated with each other during S phase.

label.value: maintenance of sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: The process in which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained as chromosomes condense, attach to the spindle in a bipolar orientation, and congress to the metaphase plate.

label.value: establishment of mitotic sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: The process in which the sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome become joined along the entire length of the chromosome during S phase during a mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: maintenance of mitotic sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: The process in which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained as chromosomes condense, attach to the spindle in a bipolar orientation, and congress to the metaphase plate during a mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: establishment of meiotic sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: The process in which the sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome become joined along the entire length of the chromosome during S phase during a meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: maintenance of meiotic sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: The process in which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained as chromosomes condense, attach to the spindle in a bipolar orientation, and congress to the metaphase plate during a meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: regulation of maintenance of sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: Any process that modulates the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained.

label.value: negative regulation of maintenance of sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: Any process that decreases the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained.

label.value: positive regulation of maintenance of sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: Any process that increases the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained.

label.value: regulation of maintenance of meiotic sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: Any process that modulates the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained during a meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: negative regulation of maintenance of meiotic sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: Any process that decreases the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained during a meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: positive regulation of maintenance of meiotic sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: Any process that increases the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained during a meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: response to cytokine

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a cytokine stimulus.

label.value: VCP-NPL4-UFD1 AAA ATPase complex

value.value: A multiprotein ATPase complex required for the efficient dislocation of ER-lumenal degradation substrates, and their subsequent proteolysis by the proteasome. In budding yeast, this complex includes Cdc48p, Npl4p and Ufd1p proteins. In mammals, this complex includes a hexamer of VCP/p97 (a cytosolic ATPase) and trimers of each of its cofactors UFD1L and NPL4 (NPLOC4) (e.g. a 6:3:3 stoichiometry).

label.value: luminal surveillance complex

value.value: A multiprotein complex that recognizes ERAD-luminal misfolded substrates and brings them to the ubiquitination/extraction machinery. In yeast, this complex consists of Yos9p, Kar2p and Hrd3p proteins.

label.value: erythrocyte homeostasis

value.value: Any process of regulating the production and elimination of erythrocytes within an organism.

label.value: erythrocyte clearance

value.value: The selective elimination of erythrocytes from the body by autoregulatory mechanisms.

definition.value: Note that this term is intended for annotation of self-gene products that lead to elimination of erythrocytes without the involvement of a symbiont.

label.value: regulation of tissue remodeling

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of tissue remodeling.

label.value: negative regulation of tissue remodeling

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of tissue remodeling.

label.value: positive regulation of tissue remodeling

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of tissue remodeling.

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate, or extent of erythrocyte clearance.

label.value: negative regulation of erythrocyte clearance

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of erythrocyte clearance.

label.value: positive regulation of erythrocyte clearance

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of erythrocyte clearance.

label.value: homotypic cell-cell adhesion

value.value: The attachment of a cell to a second cell of the identical type via adhesion molecules.

definition.value: Note that this term is not synonymous with 'homophilic cell adhesion ; GO:0007156'; the process may occur by homophilic or heterophilic mechanisms.

label.value: regulation of homotypic cell-cell adhesion

label.value: negative regulation of homotypic cell-cell adhesion

label.value: positive regulation of homotypic cell-cell adhesion

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of homotypic cell-cell adhesion.

label.value: heterotypic cell-cell adhesion

value.value: The attachment of a cell to a cell of a different type via adhesion molecules.

definition.value: Note that this term is not synonymous with 'heterophilic cell adhesion ; GO:0007157'; the process may occur by homophilic or heterophilic mechanisms.

label.value: positive regulation of heterotypic cell-cell adhesion

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of heterotypic cell-cell adhesion.

label.value: erythrocyte aggregation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate, or extent of erythrocyte aggregation.

label.value: positive regulation of erythrocyte aggregation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate, or extent of erythrocyte aggregation.
